<br>
Two weeks ago, I went to the ER down here in good ole Tennessee, and the doctor refused to give me antibiotics until I agreed to have a CT Scan. I know how much these cost, and I told the doctor I couldn't afford it. His response? &quot;We can't afford to have it be something worse and not catch it because we didn't do the scan.&quot; Are you fricking serious? I've had upwards of 25 bladder/kidney infections in the last 5 years, and I know my body pretty well. I had to go through with this CT Scan, and low and behold, there was nothing wrong with me besides a kidney infection.<br>
<br>
Got the bill today. Altogether, not including the doctor's cost, $4006.00. Four grand just for a prescription for antibiotics. I am steaming mad, and I just found out I don't qualify for state assistance for it because I &quot;make too much money.&quot; Uh huh. In order to qualify for state assistance with this, you have to make less than $745.00 a month. A person working full-time minimum wage makes more than that. Ridiculous. So, here I am, a 25-year-old who makes next to nothing, trying to go back to school in the spring, and now I have a hospital payment that cost more than my car that I have to pay back now, on top of the $20,000 in school loans that are waiting for me in deferment right now.<br>
<br>
I love our health care system. It makes me all warm and fuzzy inside.<br>
